channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: David Axelrod Throws Biden Under the Bus, Disputes Presser Claim ‘No One’, ‘No Poll’ Says He Can’t Win
5 takeaways from Biden's comeback press conference
item.description: President Biden answered a barrage of questions about his health and ability to continue leading the country on Thursday during a press conference held at the NATO conference in Washington, D.C.

item.title: Dem Donors to Withhold $90 Million Until Biden Walks
item.description: Several top donors to the Democratic Party will withhold about $90 million in promised donations unless President Joe Biden steps aside from his reelection campaign, The New York Times reported.

item.title: WATCH: Alec Baldwin's Unbelievable Reaction in the Court When Prosecutor Talks About His Motive to Lie
Schumer keeps doubts about Biden private, won't undermine POTUS publicly, Democrats say: report
item.description: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, D-N.Y. reportedly has expressed private concerns about President Biden's electoral viability but won't say so publicly.

item.title: Texas Poll: Cruz Leads Allred By 3% in Senate Race
item.description: Sen. Ted Cruz, R-Texas maintains a slim lead over Rep. Collin Allred, D-Texas, as he runs for a third term, according to a poll conducted by the University of Houston's School of Public Affairs and the School of Public Affairs at Texas Southern University.

item.title: HOT TAKES: Funny Moments/Reactions to Biden's Wild NATO Presser
Biden pressing on with ‘full bore’ schedule, despite admission he needs to slow ‘pace’
item.description: President Biden said he needs to “pace" himself, yet insisted he should take on a more robust schedule, despite concern from some members of his party about his age.

item.title: Congressional Black Caucus Backs Biden, Fears Fallout
item.description: Members of the Congressional Black Caucus - a key group of President Joe Biden's allies on Capitol Hill - fear continued pressure on Biden may prove fatal for the campaign and damage the party, according to reports. NBC News reported five caucus members say they want to see...

item.title: Biden announces that Israel and Hamas have agreed to a 'framework' for cease-fire deal: 'still work to do'
item.description: Israel initially rebuffed President Biden's deal when he announced it in May but eventually and "begrudgingly" accepted the framework of the deal as the administration kept talking with Hamas.

item.title: Turner: NATO at 75, Should We Cue the Panic?
item.description: Positive public opinion is a strong indicator of support for NATO, but public morale will determine the outcome of the war in Ukraine or any great power conflict. Public opinion has affected the political outcome of every major conflict since Korea. Our adversaries, understand that.

item.title: Ranking Member of House Intel Committee, Other Dems Deliver Blows to Biden As They Tell Him to Step Aside
Giddy House Republicans spend week lying low as Democrats implode over Biden: 'Stay out of it'
item.description: House Republicans have been elated this week to not be the center of media attention as reporters on Capitol Hill swarmed Democratic lawmakers over President Biden.

item.title: Rep. Huizenga to Newsmax: Trump Can 'Absolutely' Take Michigan
item.description: Rep. Bill Huizenga, R-Mich., told Newsmax Friday that former President Donald Trump can "absolutely" win Michigan in November's general election "and there's evidence of that all over the place."
